From: Netwrix Support <techsupport@netwrix.com>

To: Ruth-Duffy, Finn <Finn.Ruth-Duffy@TREASURY.GOV.AU>
Subject: RE: 00436872 - Endpoint Protector license and usage

Hello Finn,

I wanted to check in regarding your support ticket 00436872. We haven't heard from you in a while, and I just wanted to see if you still need assistance with this issue.

If you're still experiencing problems or have any updates to share, please let me know. If the issue has been resolved, I can go ahead and close the ticket on my end.

Please feel free to reply to this email with any updates or questions. We're here to help you get the most out of your Netwrix products.

Ticket Number: 00436872
Ticket Subject: Endpoint Protector license and usage
Ticket Details: I have a question about the Licences and Automatic Licence Renewal. Just for clarity's sake, we are still on your Emergency Licence instead of the now provided set of 1800 Licences from A23 because I wanted to get this issue sorted with Licencing first, as I am worried we do not have enough.

Okay so, within Licences we are currently showing:


When I go to Automatic Licence Renewal and set for 15 days, it has not changed any of the Used licences.
When I look through the Filters of Licences, there are none showing in any of the larger Last Seen Date selections.

However, when I go to Computers, and Filter by Licenced/Offline and Sort by oldest date seen, we have over a few thousand that have not been seen since 2020.

Sadly, from the Computers screen it looks like you cannot bulk unassign Licences. So instead what I tried was Deleting three of the oldest ones. Hoping that when I got back to Licence screen, I would see the above go to 2400.
Sadly, It is now saying 2404 and I don't know if those license were released from the ones I deleted.

Can you please let me know if I am doing something stupid and missing some options?

Thank you!

Andrei Pop
Technical Support Engineer
